Parliament, Tuesday, 2 February 2021 – The Portfolio Committee on Social Development will tomorrow receive a briefing from the Department of Social Development on its comprehensive plan pertaining to the lapsing of the temporary disability grants.
	
	The department will also update the committee on how it hopes to deal with reapplications and overcrowding at SASSA offices.
	
	Details of the briefing are as follows:
	
	Date: Wednesday, 3 February 2021
	Time: 10h00
	Venue: Zoom platform
	
	ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES.
	
	For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the Committee’s Media Officer:
